    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house closing and i'm kinda confused. what actually is escrow and why can't i just pay the seller directly?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow is a neutral third party that holds funds and documents to ensure both you and the seller are protected during the home closing process. This system prevents you from paying the seller directly before all legal contingencies are met, which could leave you liable if the deal falls through or if hidden issues are discovered. By using escrow, the funds are securely released only when all conditions of the contract are satisfied, safeguarding your financial interests throughout the transaction.",
